text: I typed up the addresses, for letters occasionally that would go above the 90th floor or higher, from Los Angeles. This was back in 1998 or 1999. I mentioned to two coworkers that I was amazed that this letter would go across country and then up so high. I was not only made fun of but ridiculed. They laughed at me. These buildings were not admired by most people at that time. Nobody back then would even think of making a movie like this. One of the coworkers, who was a russian immigrant, said he was up there and that it was no big deal even.  I left the place in 1999, so I don't know if they even remembered the conversation.
